---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
const reviewed = "June 2026";
---
<Base
  title="Company Formation & Tax in Albania 2026: SHPK & Corporate Tax | ARM Management"
  description="A current guide to setting up a company in Albania — the SHPK, the 15% corporate tax with a 0% small-business band, 20% VAT, and registration via the National Business Center, with official sources."
>
  <main>
    <section class="page-hero">
      <div class="page-hero__bg" style="background-image:url('/images/ed-zurich.jpg')"></div>
      <div class="page-hero__overlay"></div>
      <div class="page-hero__content container">
        <span class="eyebrow">Guide · Albania</span>
        <h1>Company Formation &amp; Tax in Albania</h1>
        <p>A fast-growing Adriatic market with a notable small-business break — the SHPK, a 15% corporate tax and a 0% band for smaller companies.</p>
        <div class="btn-row" style="justify-content:flex-start;margin-top:30px">
          <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary">Speak With a Senior Advisor →</a>
          <a href="/services/company-formation" class="btn-secondary">Company Formation Services</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section--warm">
      <div class="container--narrow">
        <div class="guide-meta reveal">
          <span><strong>Last reviewed:</strong> {reviewed}</span>
          <span><strong>Primary source:</strong>
            <a href="https://www.tatime.gov.al/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">General Directorate of Taxes</a>
          </span>
        </div>

        <div class="prose">
          <p class="reveal lede">Albania is an EU candidate that opened accession negotiations recently, with low costs, a modern VAT system and a distinctive corporate-tax break for smaller companies. Incorporation is handled online through a one-stop business registry, and full foreign ownership is permitted in most sectors.</p>

          <h2 class="reveal">Choosing an entity</h2>
          <p class="reveal">The standard vehicle is the <strong>SHPK</strong> (Sh.p.k., shoqëri me përgjegjësi të kufizuar, private limited company), which can be formed with symbolic capital (from ALL 100, under €1). Registration runs through the <strong>National Business Center (NBC / QKB)</strong>, accessible via the e-Albania portal, which issues the tax identification number (NIPT); name approval typically takes a day or two. Tax is then administered by the <strong>General Directorate of Taxes</strong>. Some steps, such as notarisation or bank account opening, may still call for a local representative.</p>

          <h2 class="reveal">Corporate tax and VAT</h2>
          <div class="rate-table reveal">
            <table>
              <thead><tr><th>Tax</th><th>Rate</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td>Corporate income tax (standard)</td><td>15%</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Small business (turnover ≤ ALL 14m)</td><td>0% (to end-2029)</td></tr>
                <tr><td>VAT (standard)</td><td>20%</td></tr>
                <tr><td>VAT (reduced)</td><td>6%</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Dividend withholding</td><td>8%</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
          <p class="reveal">The standard corporate income tax is <strong>15%</strong>. A notable feature is a <strong>0% rate for small businesses</strong> with annual turnover up to ALL 14,000,000 (roughly €140,000), in force through the end of 2029 under Law 29/2023 — but it is an all-or-nothing cliff: cross the threshold by any amount and the full 15% applies to the year's profit, so threshold monitoring matters. VAT is <strong>20%</strong> standard with a 6% reduced rate for tourism and accommodation. Dividends carry an 8% withholding tax. The lek is the local currency, and Albania has tax treaties with more than 40 countries.</p>

          <div class="callout reveal">
            <strong>Mind the cliff.</strong> The 0% small-business band is genuinely valuable, but because it is all-or-nothing at ALL 14m of turnover, a single lek over the line changes the whole year's bill. For anything approaching that scale, model both outcomes and watch the threshold closely.
          </div>

          <h2 class="reveal">Frequently asked questions</h2>
          <div class="reveal">
            <div class="faq-item"><h4>What is the corporate tax rate in Albania?</h4><p>15% standard, with a 0% rate for businesses whose annual turnover is up to ALL 14,000,000 (about €140,000), in force to the end of 2029.</p></div>
            <div class="faq-item"><h4>How much capital do I need for an SHPK?</h4><p>Symbolic — from ALL 100 (under €1).</p></div>
            <div class="faq-item"><h4>What is the Albanian VAT rate?</h4><p>20% standard, with a 6% reduced rate for tourism and accommodation.</p></div>
          </div>

          <h2 class="reveal">Official sources</h2>
          <ul class="sources reveal">
            <li><a href="https://www.tatime.gov.al/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">General Directorate of Taxes</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://qkb.gov.al/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">National Business Center (QKB)</a></li>
          </ul>

          <p class="reveal disclaimer">This guide is general information prepared by ARM Management and is current as at {reviewed}. It is not legal or tax advice; rules and thresholds change. Confirm against the General Directorate of Taxes, or with an advisor, before acting.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="cta-section guide-cta">
      <span class="eyebrow is-center reveal" style="justify-content:center">Speak With ARM</span>
      <h2 class="reveal">Set up in Albania with confidence.</h2>
      <p class="reveal">ARM Management advises international companies on Albanian entity formation, registration and tax compliance, alongside wider Balkan and EU structuring. Begin with a confidential conversation.</p>
      <div class="btn-row reveal">
        <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary">Schedule a Consultation →</a>
        <a href="/services/company-formation" class="btn-secondary">Company Formation Services</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Company Formation & Tax in Albania 2026","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ARM Management"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ARM Management"},"dateModified":"2026-06-01","mainEntityOfPage":"https://arm-management.com/insights/albania-company-formation"})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the corporate tax rate in Albania?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"15% standard, with a 0% rate for businesses whose annual turnover is up to ALL 14,000,000 (about €140,000), in force to the end of 2029."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How much capital do I need for an Albanian SHPK?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Symbolic — from ALL 100 (under €1)."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the Albanian VAT rate?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"20% standard, with a 6% reduced rate for tourism and accommodation."}}]})} />
</Base>
